	   <tr><td colspan=2>You're doing fine so far, but it's getting time to make a couple of changes, if you can afford to:<br><br>Start swapping out your raw silk for cured silk.&nbsp;&nbsp;Unless you tailor, this will cost about 2PP/AC (minus whatever you can sell the raw silk for).<br><br>Get rid of the split-paw tunic and get a LJ vest instead, or if you can afford 100-150PP, get a Foreman Tunic.<br><br>Trade the Screaming Mace for a Sarnak Enforcer.  Better DPS and MUCH lighter.  You may even get a bit of cash out of the trade.  Fist is just fine offhand.<br><br>Try to pick up a decent 2HB -- I always recommend the Bamboo Bo (150PP).<br><br>Get magic gloves -- any kind of magic gloves (even Netted).  If you can afford in this area, go for Gem Inlaid Gauntlets (100PP).<br><br>That's enough to work with for now and will take you into the 20s no problem.<br><br>Don't know much about Unrest, because I always heard it was a major train station and never went there.  If you're having a good time there, getting good exp and/or loot, and not dying constantly from trains, it sounds fine to me.<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
