	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hmmmm.&nbsp;&nbsp;An interesting choice you've made here.  I did a quick check of the damage tables, and near as I can figure you've basically come out even in all your trades.  At your level, 2 CoTs plus FBSS look at first glance to put out roughly the same damage as the Baton of Faith.  Didnt do all the math, so that's a rough estimate.  I was going to offer comment on your finances - Baton of Faith for 2 KDs seems to be not the best trade in the world, but that's based on my experiences on Druzzil Ro.  You also didn't give your 2HB a chance to train up it seems.<br><br>I can only offer this observation.  You CANNOT determine what the best weapon is, damage-wise, by simply observing the chat window.  There is no way to judge damage over time by doing that, and just counting dual and quad spams doesn't tell you anything useful.<br><br>I spent a decent amount of time hunting for information on this subject - it was all out there, and the nice people on this board helped me find it.  Here are the tables that give you what you need to make a real comparison.<br><br><a href="http://tinaddar.kung-foo.org/monk1hb.html" target=_new>http://tinaddar.kung-foo.org/monk1hb.html</a><br><a href="http://tinaddar.kung-foo.org/monk2hb.html" target=_new>http://tinaddar.kung-foo.org/monk2hb.html</a><br><br>monkly-business.com also has a spreadsheet that will tell you the same information.<br><br>One thing to note is that your FBSS changes the apparent delay on weapons.  The formula for new delay is:<br><br>New Delay = Old Delay / (1 + Haste)<br><br>I believe the FBSS is a 22% haste item (Osano?), so you need to divide your weapon's natural delay by 1.22.<br><br>Now would I have made this trade?  I wouldn't have thought to, but after stewing about it, I would have at a minimum sold the Baton of Faith.  It's a ten pound weapon, and guaranteed to wreak havoc on your AC and bleed out your stamina.  I don't know if I would have taken the route you did.  Would probably have held on to the KDs - I think I might have left getting the FBSS for a later time (LGuk can be attempted at lvl 40 give or take) - or spent the money on AC, but then again at level 21 I was still eating the weight penalty of carrying rusty longswords just so I could sell them for a couple gold.  The items you're discussing are WAY beyond the means of the non-twinked at those levels.  You don't mention how you managed to come by with 4K at level 21, so if you found some way of making really good cash in the 20s, please share.<br><br>Keyeluke<br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 45th Circle<br>Strange Brew<br>Druzzil Ro<br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a><br>Dripsy - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922</a></td></tr>
