	   <tr><td colspan=2>Tailoring is possibly the hardest trade skill to learn - goes up very slowly and you can't just spend lots of money to do it.&nbsp;&nbsp;You either need to harvest the raw materials yourself or buy them off other PCs.  Right here on Allakhazam there are links to tailoring sites - click on the Skills link at left.  <br><br>You need brewing to make Heady Kiola, which is then used to make cured silk armor.<br><br>Here is one link - there are many others - with recipes and instructions:<br><br><a href="http://everquest.allakhazam.com/Skills/Tailoring_Xekl_Guide.htm" target=_new>http://everquest.allakhazam.com/Skills/Tailoring_Xekl_Guide.htm</a><br><br>Tailoring is a long and tough road.  I've killed a whole lot of spiders and a whole lot of cats, wolves, and bears, and I'm up 38.  Joy.<br><br>Keyeluke <br>Monk of the Silent Fist, 44th Circle <br>Strange Brew <br>Druzzil Ro <br><br>&nbsp;<br>Keyeluke - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=27415</a><br>Dripsy - <a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922" target=_new>http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=227922</a></td></tr>
