	   <a name=99196677951879></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f99196677951879><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99196677951879>RE: Newbie items</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=3&mid=99196677951879#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=39551><span id=Guru>Osano</span></a>, <span id=Guru>Guru</span><br><span id=notbold>171 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Jun 7th 10:19 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[4.90]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Serp Bracers are a bit better than silver plated, but you should be looking for Vox Bracers (Sybols of Loyalty to Vox).&nbsp;&nbsp;With 7AC and only 0.3 wt, these are the mid-level monk's bracers of choice.  They should run you 150PP or less per pair.<br><br>The bo stick is fine if you're training 2HB in a group and not getting much aggro, so you won't have to worry about the weight.  For soloing (or getting aggro in a group) with 2HB, get a Bamboo Bo.  8/20, so a bit worse ratio than the Bo, but only 1.0 wt. and your 2HB will go up more quickly as it's faster.  The bamboo bo runs around 150PP.  Most monks only use 2HB to train with until they manage to get one of the uber-2HB much later in life.  The adamantine bo (aka suicide stick) is a great value at about 750 - 1000PP (even less on some servers), because most people don't care to learn how to deal with the AOE proc.  I picked one of these up when my bamboo bo just wasn't good enough to train with after level 35, and I love it.  Basically, don't worry too much about 2HB except for keeping your skill up, unless and until you can afford one of the big sticks, which is not likely to happen until you're much higher in level if you're untwinked.<br><br>If you've got a mix of cured and Wu's, you're doing great at 15.  Drake Hide Legs have a great black look and are nearly as good as Wu's, but with +5Dex -- you'll give up some AC for Dex with these.  Until Wu's, these were the mid-level monk's legs of choice, until Gatorscale was affordable.  Drake Hide ran about 200PP, but may have come down since Wu's came out -- I haven't checked the market recently.  Other good cost effective add-ons -- Gem Inlaid Gauntlets (100PP), Thick Leather Apron (25PP), Drolvarg Mantle (150PP).  For Boots and Cloak, you can't beat the Wu's without spending quite a lot of cash.<br><br>Good Luck.<br>&nbsp;<br>Osano<br>Level 44 Human Monk<br>Tholuxe-Paells</td></tr>
